B.Sc. Catering Science & Hotel Management

Catering Science and Hotel Management department is a member of HERA ,The Hoteliers, Educators & Recruiters Association. It has well â€“ equipped laboratories and enjoys cordial relationship with industry and leading chains of hotels.

B.Sc., in Catering Science & Hotel Management is a three year degree course comprising of six semesters.

Special Features

B.Sc., Catering students are required to study French as their Language under Part I. In addition to regular laboratory sessions, Students also gain hands-on experience through food festivals, special workshops on vegetable carving, flower arrangements and other cookery competitions.

Internship Students are required to complete an industrial training for four months in the different departments of five star hotels. The department also offers assured placement assistance in reputed leading hotel chains in India and abroad.

Course Content

  Food Production

  Food and Beverage Service

  Bakery and Confectionary

  House Keeping Management

  Front Office Operations

  Tourism Management

  Communicative English & French

  Computer Application

  Hotel Accounts
